     * Access to diagnostics

We increase vulnerable populations’ access to diagnostics
       By strengthening clinical laboratories in national healthcare
       systems, we want to enhance the quality of, and access to, clinical
       diagnosis, the backbone of any strategy aimed at preventing disease
       and improving patient care.
       Find out more
     * Applied research

We enhance local applied research capabilities
       By training scientists, developing collaborative programs and
       creating laboratories of excellence, we support researchers in
       developing countries.
       Find out more
     * Knowledge-sharing

We foster knowledge-sharing and public health initiatives
       We want to disseminate scientific innovation in the field of
       infectious disease worldwide, leveraging Les Pensières Center for
       Global Health, a place for meetings, courses and North-South
       dialogue about public health.
       Find out more
     * Mothers & children

We support mothers and children
       Taking a global health approach, we work with Fondation Christophe
       et Rodolphe Mérieux to improve the quality of life for mothers and
       children, who are particularly vulnerable to infectious diseases.
       Find out more

   About us

   Our mission is to fight the infectious diseases that affect vulnerable
   populations in developing countries, especially mothers and children,
   by building local capacities.

   IFRAME: https://www.youtube.com/embed/2xfjh4DZhYg?rel=0&showinfo=0

   Discover the Mérieux Foundation: 50 years of fighting infectious
   diseases
